                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: possibly ʾabuna Tasfā [Yonas]. ʾabuna Tasfā [Yonas] (the
                        second part of the name is barely legible) is mentioned as the scribe on
                           <locus target="#10va">10va</locus>.<date>18th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፍ፡</abbr> for <expan>ፍቱሐ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#33va">33va</locus>b, 34rab)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ካ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ካሕን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#34vb">34vb</locus>, 35ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ዲ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#37va">37va</locus>, 57va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ሕ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበሉ፡ ሕዝብ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#37va">37va</locus>b, 57va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ተክለ፡ ሃይማ(ኖ)፡</abbr> for <expan>ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#11va">11va</locus>, 12rb)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ተክለ፡ ሚካኤ፡</abbr> for <expan>ተክለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#13vb">13vb</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the
                           scribe; name of the king; a few lines on the incipit page of the Text,
                           alternating with black lines; incipit of each section of the text;
                           abbreviations; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; some other words, e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 4rb, 4vb, 5ra),
                           ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 9va, 11va), nǝbäl (e.g., fols. 9vb, 10va), wa-kāʿǝba
                           (e.g., fols. 10ra, 11ra), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 37vb), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g.,
                           fols. 70vab, 71rab).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Possibly different hands were involved
                        in the copying
                        process.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">f. 1va</locus>
                           <desc>: Text about the Trinity (?)</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">f.1va: በአካል፡ ማዓፈጠራቹ፡ ስላሴ፡ ስላሴ፡ ስንትምናቸው፡ አንድም፡ ናቸው፡
                              ሶስት፡ ናቸው፡ ሰስትነታቸው፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in Amharic. The Trinity is mentioned. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Erasures: e.g., <locus target="#16va">16va</locus>,
                           27ra, 87va.
 - Omitted letters or words are written interlineally or
                           in the margin: e.g., <locus target="#14ra">14ra</locus>, 25rb, 26vb,
                           27vb, 31va.
 - The scribe used compressed script: <locus from="108va" to="112va">108va-112va</locus>.
 - The word እገሌ is marked above
                           and below by dashes in red and black ink: e.g., <locus target="#52vb">52vb</locus>, 53rab, 53vab, 54rab, or by thin lines, e.g. <locus target="#103va">103va</locus>b, 104rab.
 - Pen trial: 113v.
 -
                           Scribbles and doodles: e.g., <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 112v, 113r,
                           114r, 114v.
 - Sign, in the shape of a cross with a loop at the end
                           of each arm, written in the margin: <locus target="#29v">29v</locus>,
                           69r, 93v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes written in a secondary hand in the upper
                              margin referring to the content of the Ms.: e.g., fols. 8r, 28v, 29v,
                              33v, 38r, 42r, 43v, 48r. - Threads have been inserted in the upper
                              corner or outer margin of fols. 37, 58, 64, 69, 73, 79, 85, 88, 89,
                              91, 102.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
