               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0050MSM">Mänäbäyti Ṣǝyon Māryām/ MSM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1745" notAfter="1800">King Takla Giyorgis (possibly Takla
                        Giyorgis I, r. 1779-1800 with interruptions; cf. EAE IV, 826) is mentioned
                        on <locus target="#70ra">70ra</locus>. Patriarch ʾabbā Marqos and
                        Metropolitan ʾabbā Yoḥannǝs are mentioned on <locus target="#69vb">69vb</locus>. Mark VII was the patriarch of Alexandria in 1745-69.
                        Yoḥannǝs III was the metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1744-61 (cf. EAE V,
                        71).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot is mentioned in the
                     supplication formulas, e.g., on 10va, 11ra, 11va,
                     13ra, 16ra; Takla Mikāʾel is mentioned, e.g., on 11vab, 23ra, 103rab.</provenance></history>
